Bonneville offers no on - peak power for Wednesday . Bonneville Power Administration ( BPA ) offered no on - peak power for Wednesday schedulings while raising prices for off - peak offers by $ 2 . 00 to $ 3 . 50 per megawatt hour ( MWh ) , the agency said Tuesday . BPA also limited firm offers during off - peak hours to 400 megawatts and non - firm volumes to 300 MW , compared with no limits on off - peak Tuesday sales . The federal agency offered firm power during off - peak hours ( 0100 - 0600 and 230 - 2400 PST ) on Wednesday at $ 19 . 00 per MWh for all deliveries , up from $ 16 . 00 for Tuesday . Non - firm power , again for both Northwest and California - Oregon border deliveries , was offered at $ 18 . 50 for hours ending 0100 - 0500 and 2400 , up from $ 16 . 50 . Non - firm power during hours ending 0600 and 2300 on Wednesday was offered at $ 22 . 00 per MWh , compared with $ 18 . 50 for Tuesday . - - Los Angeles bureau + 1 213 955 6761 
